The paper discusses a method for analyzing the publication habits of a specific scientific community, specifically researchers in Bibliometrics, using Google Scholar Citations. This involves processing the top 1000 most cited documents by these authors and analyzing their publication venues. This falls under the sub-categories of Digital Libraries (cs.DL), Information Retrieval (cs.IR), Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), Computers and Society (cs.CY), and Cryptography and Security (cs.CR). However, given the focus on bibliometrics and citation analysis, cs.DL and cs.IR are the most likely sub-categories.
